{"title_page": "Anne McElvoy", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Anne McElvoy\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              =File:Anne McElvoy 2019.jpg\n| caption            = McElvoy at the Horasis Global Meeting in 2019\n\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1965|06|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[County Durham]], England<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.freebmd.org.uk/cgi/information.pl?cite=F1GhHY5wmSf2SOM9M7Pe1Q&scan=1|title=Index entry|accessdate=28 February 2018|work=FreeBMD|publisher=ONS}}</ref>\n| residence          = \n| nationality        = [[British people|British]]\n| other_names        = \n| education          = [[St Bede's Catholic School and Sixth Form College|St Bede's Catholic School, Lanchester]]\n| alma_mater         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Wadham College, Oxford]]\n* [[Humboldt University of Berlin]]\n}}\n| occupation         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Journalist]]\n* [[News presenter|Broadcaster]]\n}}\n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| influences         = \n| influenced         = \n| home_town          = \n| television         = \n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Martin Ivens]]|1994}}\n| children           = Benjamin Ivens, Gabriel Ivens and Isolde Ivens\n| parents            = Alexander McElvoy<br>Mary Margaret Bartley/McElvoy\n| relatives          = \n| awards             = \n| website            = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n}}\n\n'''Anne McElvoy''' (born 25 June 1965) is a British journalist, contributing to ''[[The Economist]]'' and the ''[[London Evening Standard]]'', and the [[BBC]].<ref name=\"whoislog\">{{cite web|url=http://www.whoislog.info/profile/anne-mcelvoy.html|title=Anne McElvoy - Biorgrpahy and facts|last=|first=|date=|website=www.whoislog.info|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103113227/http://www.whoislog.info/profile/anne-mcelvoy.html|archive-date=2014-11-03|url-status = dead|access-date=2014-11-03}}</ref>{{Circular reference|date=January 2018}}\n\n==Early life==\nMcElvoy attended [[St Bede's Catholic School and Sixth Form College|St Bede's RC Comprehensive School]] in [[Lanchester, County Durham]], and read German and Philosophy at [[Wadham College, Oxford]]. While at [[Oxford University]], she edited ''[[Cherwell newspaper|Cherwell]]'', the student newspaper. She spent a year at the [[Humboldt University of Berlin]], then in [[East Berlin]], studying [[Literature of East Germany|East German literature]] and censorship.\n\n==Career==\n===Newspapers===\nShe joined ''The Times'' in 1988 as a graduate trainee,writing frequently about the dissolution of eastern Europe, and later reporting from Moscow. In 1995 she became deputy editor of ''[[The Spectator]]'', as well as being a columnist on its sister publication, ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''.<ref name=\"whoislog\" />{{Circular reference|date=January 2018}}\n[[File:Anne McElvoy 2017.jpg|thumb|left|McElvoy at the Horasis Global Meeting in 2017]]\n\nIn 1997 she became associate editor of ''The Independent''. In 2002 she moved to the <!-- Did not acquire the London prefix until 2009. -->''[[Evening Standard]]'' as executive editor remaining until 2009, though McElvoy still contributes a weekly political column. In 2009 she joined ''[[The Economist]]''.\nShe assisted [[Markus Wolf]] in the writing of ''Man Without A Face: The Autobiography Of Communism's Greatest Spymaster'' and ''Memoirs Of A Spymaster: The Man Who Waged A Secret War Against The West'', and ''The Saddled Cow: East Germany's Life And Legacy''.\n\n===Broadcasting===\nShe has been a regular presenter of the [[BBC Radio 3]] late-night discussion programme since 2009, initially on ''[[Night Waves]]'', and then its successor programme, ''Free Thinking''. She has also appeared on BBC2's ''[[The Review Show|Newsnight Review]]'', and occasionally contributes to [[BBC Radio 4]]'s ''[[The Moral Maze]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mediadirectory.economist.com/people/anne-mcelvoy/|title=Anne McElvoy}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 1994, McElvoy married [[Martin Ivens]], also a journalist, who is the editor of ''[[The Sunday Times]]''. The couple have two sons and one daughter.\n\n==Publications==\n* {{cite book|last=McElvoy|first=Anne|authormask=2 | title=The Saddled Cow: East Germany's Life & Legacy | isbn = 978-0571165919 | publisher = [[Faber and Faber]] | year= 1992}}\n* {{cite book|last=McElvoy|first=Anne|authormask=2 | title=Man Without A Face: The Autobiography of Communism's Greatest Spymaster | isbn = 978-0224044981 | publisher = [[Jonathan Cape|Jonathan Cape Ltd]] | year= 1997}}\n* {{cite book|last=McElvoy|first=Anne|authormask=2 | title=Memoirs Of A Spymaster: The Man Who Waged a Secret War Against the West| isbn = 978-0712666558 | publisher = [[Pimlico Books at Random House|Pimlico]] | year= 1998 }}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Twitter}}\n* {{Journalisted}}\n* [https://www.theguardian.com/profile/anne-mcelvoy Guardian profile]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110811230141/http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/standard-home/columnistarchive/Anne%20McElvoy-columnist-184-archive.do Evening Standard]\n* [http://www.newstatesman.com/writers/anne_mcelvoy New Statesman]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/newsnight/review/7316853.stm Newsnight Review]\n* [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00zzplm What The Papers Say]\n\n===Video clips===\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-12936440 ''This Week'' April 2011]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEcyB0zcVEM ''The Review Show'' November 2010]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/the_daily_politics/8564449.stm ''Daily Politics'' March 2010]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/the_daily_politics/8506335.stm ''Daily Politics'' February 2010]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:McElvoy, Anne}}\n[[Category:1965 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Alumni of Wadham College, Oxford]]\n[[Category:British journalists]]\n[[Category:Humboldt University of Berlin alumni]]\n[[Category:People from County Durham]]\n[[Category:People from Lanchester, County Durham]]\n[[Category:The Economist people]]\n[[Category:The Times people]]\n\n\n{{UK-journalist-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=September 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| honorific_prefix   = \n| name               = Anne McElvoy\n| honorific_suffix   = \n| image              =File:Anne McElvoy 2019.jpg\n| caption            = McElvoy at the Horasis Global Meeting in 2019\n\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|1965|06|25|df=y}}\n| birth_place        = [[County Durham]], England<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.freebmd.org.uk/cgi/information.pl?cite=F1GhHY5wmSf2SOM9M7Pe1Q&scan=1|title=Index entry|accessdate=28 February 2018|work=FreeBMD|publisher=ONS}}</ref>\n| residence          = \n| nationality        = [[British people|British]]\n| other_names        = \n| education          = [[St Bede's Catholic School and Sixth Form College|St Bede's Catholic School, Lanchester]]\n| alma_mater         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Wadham College, Oxford]]\n* [[Humboldt University of Berlin]]\n}}\n| occupation         = {{Plainlist|\n* [[Journalist]]\n* [[News presenter|Broadcaster]]\n}}\n| employer           = \n| organization       = \n| agent              = \n| known_for          = \n| notable_works      = \n| style              = \n| influences         = \n| influenced         = \n| home_town          = \n| television         = \n| spouse             = {{marriage|[[Martin Ivens]]|1994}}\n| children           = Benjamin Ivens, Gabriel Ivens and Isolde Ivens\n| parents            = Alexander McElvoy<br>Mary Margaret Bartley/McElvoy\n| relatives          = \n| awards             = \n| website            = <!-- {{URL|www.example.com}} -->\n}}\n\n'''Anne McElvoy''' (born 25 June 1965) is a British journalist, contributing to ''[[The Economist]]'' and the ''[[London Evening Standard]]'', and the [[BBC]].<ref name=\"whoislog\">{{cite web|url=http://www.whoislog.info/profile/anne-mcelvoy.html|title=Anne McElvoy - Biorgrpahy and facts|last=|first=|date=|website=www.whoislog.info|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141103113227/http://www.whoislog.info/profile/anne-mcelvoy.html|archive-date=2014-11-03|url-status = dead|access-date=2014-11-03}}</ref>{{Circular reference|date=January 2018}}\n\n==Early life==\nMcElvoy attended [[St Bede's Catholic School and Sixth Form College|St Bede's RC Comprehensive School]] in [[Lanchester, County Durham]], and read German and Philosophy at [[Wadham College, Oxford]]. While at [[Oxford University]], she edited ''[[Cherwell newspaper|Cherwell]]'', the student newspaper. She spent a year at the [[Humboldt University of Berlin]], then in [[East Berlin]], studying [[Literature of East Germany|East German literature]] and censorship.\n\n==Career==\n===Newspapers===\nShe joined ''The Times'' in 1988 as a graduate trainee, heavily covering the dissolution of eastern Europe, and later reporting from Moscow. In 1995 she became deputy editor of ''[[The Spectator]]'', as well as being a columnist on its sister publication, ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]''.<ref name=\"whoislog\" />{{Circular reference|date=January 2018}}\n[[File:Anne McElvoy 2017.jpg|thumb|left|McElvoy at the Horasis Global Meeting in 2017]]\n\nIn 1997 she became associate editor of ''The Independent''. In 2002 she moved to the <!-- Did not acquire the London prefix until 2009. -->''[[Evening Standard]]'' as executive editor remaining until 2009, though McElvoy still contributes a weekly political column. In 2009 she joined ''[[The Economist]]''.\nShe assisted [[Markus Wolf]] in the writing of ''Man Without A Face: The Autobiography Of Communism's Greatest Spymaster'' and ''Memoirs Of A Spymaster: The Man Who Waged A Secret War Against The West'', and ''The Saddled Cow: East Germany's Life And Legacy''.\n\n===Broadcasting===\nShe has been a regular presenter of the [[BBC Radio 3]] late-night discussion programme since 2009, initially on ''[[Night Waves]]'', and then its successor programme, ''Free Thinking''. She has also appeared on BBC2's ''[[The Review Show|Newsnight Review]]'', and occasionally contributes to [[BBC Radio 4]]'s ''[[The Moral Maze]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mediadirectory.economist.com/people/anne-mcelvoy/|title=Anne McElvoy}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn 1994, McElvoy married [[Martin Ivens]], also a journalist, who is the editor of ''[[The Sunday Times]]''. The couple have two sons and one daughter.\n\n==Publications==\n* {{cite book|last=McElvoy|first=Anne|authormask=2 | title=The Saddled Cow: East Germany's Life & Legacy | isbn = 978-0571165919 | publisher = [[Faber and Faber]] | year= 1992}}\n* {{cite book|last=McElvoy|first=Anne|authormask=2 | title=Man Without A Face: The Autobiography of Communism's Greatest Spymaster | isbn = 978-0224044981 | publisher = [[Jonathan Cape|Jonathan Cape Ltd]] | year= 1997}}\n* {{cite book|last=McElvoy|first=Anne|authormask=2 | title=Memoirs Of A Spymaster: The Man Who Waged a Secret War Against the West| isbn = 978-0712666558 | publisher = [[Pimlico Books at Random House|Pimlico]] | year= 1998 }}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Twitter}}\n* {{Journalisted}}\n* [https://www.theguardian.com/profile/anne-mcelvoy Guardian profile]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20110811230141/http://www.thisislondon.co.uk/standard-home/columnistarchive/Anne%20McElvoy-columnist-184-archive.do Evening Standard]\n* [http://www.newstatesman.com/writers/anne_mcelvoy New Statesman]\n* [http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/programmes/newsnight/review/7316853.stm Newsnight Review]\n* [http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00zzplm What The Papers Say]\n\n===Video clips===\n* [https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-12936440 ''This Week'' April 2011]\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cEcyB0