August 2012|access-date=23 October 2017|via=YouTube|quote=I really am and I've always been a Saint Lucian.}}</ref> Born in [[Saint Lucia]], he moved to the United Kingdom when he was nine years old, and grew up in [[Peckham]], [[South London]]. Marcell lives in [[Banstead]], Surrey.\n\nHe studied theatre and science at the [[University of Sheffield]], then took courses in speech and dance at the [[Royal Central School of Speech and Drama|Central School of Speech and Drama]].\n\n==Career==\nAs a member of the [[Royal Shakespeare Company]], he appeared in productions of ''[[Othello]]'' and ''[[A Midsummer Night's Dream]]''. He has also appeared often on British television and in feature films. He serves on the board of the [[Shakespeare's Globe Theatre]] in London, where he featured in a nationwide production of Shakespeare's ''[[Much Ado About Nothing]]'', and ''[[King Lear]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.shakespearesglobe.com/education/discovery-space/adopt-an-actor/archive/king-lear-played-by-joseph-marcell |work=[[Shakespeare's Globe]] |title=King Lear Played by Joseph Marcell |year=2013 |access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sanluisobispo.com/entertainment/arts-culture/article39503550.html |title=Joseph Marcell goes from 'Fresh Prince' to 'King Lear' |first=Sarah |last=Linn |date=12 November 2014 |access-date=24 March 2019 |newspaper=[[Sanluisobispo.com]]}}</ref> \n\nIn May 2016, he played Gonzalo in the play by Shakespeare ''[[The Tempest]]'' at [[Sam Wanamaker Playhouse]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03tmv05 |title=Joseph Marcell as Gonzalo \u2013 The Tempest |date=9 May 2016 |access-date=24 March 2019 |work=[[BBC Programmes]] |publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.shakespearesglobe.com/discovery-space/adopt-an-actor/archive/gonzalo-played-by-joseph-marcell |title=Gonzalo Played by Joseph Marcell |year=2016 |access-date=24 March 2019 |work=[[Shakespeare's Globe]]}}</ref> and Solly Two Kings in the play by [[August Wilson]] ''[[Gem of the Ocean]]'' at [[Tricycle Theatre]] in London.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/theatre-dance/reviews/gem-of-the-ocean-tricycle-theatre-london-6111908.html |title=Gem of the Ocean, Tricycle Theatre, London <!-- none onestar twostar threestar fourstar fivestar --> |first=Paul |last=Taylor |date=13 January 2016 |access-date=24 March 2019 |newspaper=[[Independent (newspaper)|Independent]]}}</ref> In July 2017, Marcell began rehearsals as Titus Andronicus for the La Grande Shakespeare Company in La Grande, Oregon.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.lagrandeobserver.com/newsroomstafflist/5474119-151/fresh-face-joins-local-production |title='Fresh' face joins local production |first=Emily |last=Adair |date=26 January 2017 |access-date=24 March 2019 |newspaper=[[La Grande Observer]] |publisher=A [[Western Communications]] Company}}</ref>\n\n==Film and television==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Title\n!Role\n!Notes\n|-\n|1974\n|''[[Antony and Cleopatra (1974 TV drama)|Antony and Cleopatra]]''\n|Eros\n|\n|-\n|1978\u20131979\n|''[[Empire Road]]''\n|Walter Isaacs\n|15 episodes\n|-\n|1980 \n|''[[The Professionals (TV series)|The Professionals]]''\n|Nero\n|Credited as Joe Marcell\n|-\n|1983 \n|''[[Rumpole of the Bailey]]''\n|Freddy Ruingo\n|\n|-\n|1985 \n|''[[Juliet Bravo]]''\n|Bold\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''[[Playing Away]]''\n|\n|\n|-\n|1987\n|''[[Cry Freedom]]''\n|Moses\n|\n|-\n|1988 \n|''[[Doctor Who]]''\n|John\n|Episode: \"[[Remembrance of the Daleks]]\"\n|-\n|1989 \n|''[[Boon (TV series)|Boon]]''\n|Charlie Fowkes\n|\n|-\n|1990\n|''[[Desmond's]]''\n|Matthew McFarlane\n|\n|-\n|1990\u20131996\n|''[[The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air]]''\n|[[Geoffrey Butler (The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air)|Geoffrey Butler]]\n| 146 episodes\n|-\n|1992\n|''[[EastEnders]]''\n|[[Adrian Bell (EastEnders)|Adrian Bell]]\n|2 episodes\n|-\n|1993\n|''[[David Copperfield (1993 film)|David Copperfield]]''\n|Mr. Micawber (voice)\n|\n|