nuary 2018}}</ref>\n*''[[The Tempest]]'' (2016) as Gonzalo, [[Sam Wanamaker Playhouse]], London <ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/theatre/what-to-see/the-tempest-is-a-magical-last-bow-for-dominic-dromgoole/ |title=The Tempest is a magical last bow for the Globe's Dominic Dromgoole |first=Dominic |last=Cavendish |date=24 February 2016 |access-date=24 March 2019 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |publisher=[[Telegraph Media Group Limited]]}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb name|0545186}}\n* [http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/interviews/a553016/what-happened-to-geoffrey-from-the-fresh-prince-of-bel-air.html#~oFye6oGXoLW0J0 Alex Fletcher, \"What happened to Geoffrey from The Fresh Prince of Bel-Air?\"], TV interview, Digital Spy, 24 February 2014.\n* [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UfmpNvi-_bM \"Caribbean Footsteps meets with Joseph Marcell\"]. YouTube\n* \"What the butler did next\" [http://www.kreolmagazine.com/arts-culture/spotlight/joseph-marcell-what-the-butler-did-next/]\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Marcell, Joseph}}\n[[Category:English male film actors]]\n[[Category:English male television actors]]\n[[Category:1948 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Male actors from London]]\n[[Category:English people of Saint Lucian descent]]\n[[Category:Saint Lucian emigrants to the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Black English male actors]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the University of Sheffield]]\n[[Category:Alumni of the Royal Central School of Speech and Drama]]\n[[Category:British male Shakespearean actors]]\n[[Category:20th-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:21st-century English male actors]]\n[[Category:People from Southall]]\n[[Category:Saint Lucian actors]]\n[[Category:Royal Shakespeare Company members]]\n", "name_user": "51.37.3.232", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Joseph_Marcell"}
